<subSubSection id="C0BEE63B2B50DA8F04EC86D9D5AAC1C2" pageId="null" pageNumber="518" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="CE7D6F1576DBFE7D6A6DD925B93937AE" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
<taxonomicName id="E7EF173F1012E64DFBC7664DA7769B29" authority="L." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Helianthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="518" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflorus">
Helianthus 
<normalizedToken id="E0C95069AB97EB4C117A89F2B2E034E9" originalValue="multiflórus" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">multiflorus</normalizedToken>
<authorityName id="F0F9A0A24EE106806A6B5E539322B485" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">L.</authorityName>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3172E3C64B643AD712F118A2C5BA8FBC" pageId="null" pageNumber="518" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="CEE69F7475A8F96F59606CEC555F366E" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Vielstrahlige Sonnenblume</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="6D6AFB3A26488F52CFA4C3577BD26FF0" pageId="null" pageNumber="518" type="description">
<paragraph id="EB1DC0C39825686800B7BEAE6AE17674" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
Rhizom lang, meist ohne Knollen; Pflanze 1-2,5 m hoch. Stengel im untern Teil fast kahl, nicht rauh. 
<normalizedToken id="8B43A23BA42AF788CFECD2958AC56DB3" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
grob 
<normalizedToken id="9682E745B0715FE06F706DC8652CA20D" originalValue="gezähnt" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">gezaehnt</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="A8218B1FE5C190217A7E8B3E459295CC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
<normalizedToken id="337DC8E4638F5C230709532F50B64249" originalValue="Zähne" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Zaehne</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="481D0CFA381345F371FCD32E76511B0E" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">laenger</normalizedToken>
als 2 mm
</emphasis>
), 
<emphasis id="3E0045295717137E4043BAF129615146" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
die 
<normalizedToken id="BF2992DDA789024BAE33797B3CAC8E0D" originalValue="grö" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">groe</normalizedToken>
&amp;szligten 5
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="9679759384FA66F06E1E0CA79A44DA6E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">8 cm breit</emphasis>
, unterseits mit 3 vorspringenden Nerven. 
<normalizedToken id="C7569D7DBF97CA44A60F5361CE3AB424" originalValue="Hüllblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Huellblaetter</normalizedToken>
abstehend oder 
<normalizedToken id="B4BCB8CD3A4A22637408B90A85C95E73" originalValue="zurückgebogen" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">zurueckgebogen</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis id="89A0B83DC3F99A1E1F439EC535A156A9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">2</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="A7E239C7AE2A7561A43EFDB513207413" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
4 mm breit. 
<normalizedToken id="9E1E0299F07E059C78A75B6A6D99A37E" originalValue="Zungenförmige" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Zungenfoermige</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="081AB3B95DBE4D553B6250013E065E9C" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Blueten</normalizedToken>
20
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="C8B22EF68C72E65D84468BBC74B9F7CF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">40, 2,5</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="3F6C74029A41FA4C2E47800A25E4933B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
4 cm lang. Scheibe mit den 
<normalizedToken id="772517DCDE92A14846268E4E371E2E27" originalValue="Röhrenblüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Roehrenblueten</normalizedToken>
im Durchmesser 2
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="CE75DAF1F623C7393EEDE4D999346607" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">2,5 cm.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="45BE4C894E99CBEB2CBC00EB6AE2C8BA" originalValue="Röhrenblüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Roehrenblueten</normalizedToken>
kahl. - 
<normalizedToken id="7211DC707E3E6EC08DB722AB9A5057D3" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="0F4735F341603AEF981CDE5EBC6B90FD" originalValue="Später" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Spaeter</normalizedToken>
Sommer und Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F024195EC2195831BCC5C67DA7DBDC9" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="4D86B5267C91C280C4D4C7CAE78A857F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="887FAC103E6FB2F3F3B6E12F6860BBC0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">51:</emphasis>
Material aus 
<normalizedToken id="CF335C0A1EEF31C76F88AAB89A6F2F04" originalValue="Gärten" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Gaerten</normalizedToken>
(Heiser und Smith 1960), 
<normalizedToken id="E6C19C87644F11A9ED2EA7170EB6CA5C" originalValue="±" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">+/-</normalizedToken>
steril.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0854A18C7A32525CC63534BD3F75B5E7" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="727FFCCEE8F3D03941202406206941F2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin. Feuchte, lockere, sandige 
<normalizedToken id="821AB22D5B78F4C57C2DC5C90ABB50BA" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Boeden</normalizedToken>
. Flu&amp;szligufer, 
<normalizedToken id="2A61EF08CC310B9762DE55AEAEF7A32D" originalValue="Auenwälder" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Auenwaelder</normalizedToken>
, Kiesgruben. 
<emphasis id="2F28BDEE8F4852F615CBD21AE89AE537" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Impatienti-Solidaginetum</emphasis>
Moor 1958.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3762E2A9F5319BF1D38E09B8682D9678" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="A955E4ACAE2651D1C0D3E4D129E4F465" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">Verbreitung.</emphasis>
Siehe Bemerkungen. - Im Gebiet zerstreut, ziemlich selten.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="452E305EEC2F0D1DE4C8B7079837DB2F" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="9DDF21D27EC86AB14E8EB42B0B002B0B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">
Bemerkungen. 
<taxonomicName id="E36BBDD7C851BB7B9F6479280CFE9F90" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Helianthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="518" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflorus">H. multiflorus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
wird von Heiser und Smith (1960) als Bastard zwischen 
<taxonomicName id="ED10D87C7ACA45F42495F86172D52F66" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Helianthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="518" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="annuus">
<emphasis id="14FB6A767E8F3E674385FEDED7E5FA70" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">H. annuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2n = 34) und 
<taxonomicName id="425EE0F4430E4F8C3950F62A868F8521" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Helianthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="518" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decapetalus">
<emphasis id="723445E2FEB6892716D37CD72ACF7FB9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="518">H. decapetalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2n = 68) gedeutet und konnte von ihnen auch experimentell hergestellt werden. Die Sippe ist als Zierpflanze nach Europa gekommen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
